<TITLE> 22 BTCL officials face Tk 40cr graft charges </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 15 (bdnews24.com) - The Anticorruption Commission will file 11 separate cases against 22 officials of Bangladesh Telecommunications Company Limited for embezzlement totalling Tk 40 crore. "The BTCL (former BTTB) employees misappropriated the amount through fraudulent means in two separate phases," ACC director general Colonel Hanif Iqbal said on Monday. Tk 32.55 crore was embezzled showing counterfeit bill-vouchers for the company's transport repair works from 2000-2001 to 2006-2007, Iqbal told reporters at a regular briefing. "The ACC has given approval to file seven cases against 13 officials, including divisional engineer Raich-ur-Rahman, for their involvement," he said. The ACC has also approved four more cases against another nine officials for misappropriation of Tk 8.07 crore citing "transport costs". bdnews
